{"lemma":"أَكْبَرَيْ","slug":"أَكْبَرَيْ","root":"ك.ب.ر","root_slug":"ك-ب-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ك-ب-ر","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"أَكْبَر","root":"كبر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":24},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n36586","n36587"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D9%83%D9%92%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"elative degree of كَبِير (kabīr):; greater; greatest","examples":[{"text":"اللّٰهُ أَكْبَر","english":"God (Allah) is greater / the greatest"}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"elative degree of كَبِير (kabīr):; bigger, larger; biggest, largest"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"elative degree of كَبِير (kabīr):; older, elder; oldest, eldest"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"greater (Of two, or rarely more than two, things: the larger in size (bigger), in value, in importance etc)","examples":[{"text":"شِرْك أَصْغَر / شِرْكٌ أَكْبَر"},{"text":"فَاصِلَة صُغْرَى / فَاصِلَة كُبْرَى"}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"senior (age, rank, etc.)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to deem great"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Elative of كَبِير (kabīr, “big, great, powerful”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n36586","headword_ar":"اَكْبَرُ","root":"kbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Greater,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"greatest, in body,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"corporeal substance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in estimation"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rank"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dignity:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"more,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most, advanced in age; older,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"oldest:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuboraY","text_ar":"كُبْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Msb:) pl. masc."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akaAbiru","text_ar":"اَكَابِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akobaruwna","text_ar":"اَكْبَرُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuborN","text_ar":"كُبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", because this is of a form specially appropriated to an epithet such as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asowadu","text_ar":"اَسْوَدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHomaru","text_ar":"اَحْمَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and you do not use"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Akbr","text_ar":"اكبر"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the manner of such an epithet, for you do not say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA rajulN A^akobaru","text_ar":"هٰذَا رَجُلٌ اَكْبَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", unless you conjoin it with a following word by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino","text_ar":"مِنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or prefix to it the article"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) [but see the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daEaA bikuborihi","text_ar":"دَعَا بِكُبْرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below:] the pl. fem. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kubarN","text_ar":"كُبَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuborayaAtN","text_ar":"كُبْرَيَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akobaru","text_ar":"اَكْبَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also used in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kabiyrN","text_ar":"كَبِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) accord. to some,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aall~`hu A^akobar","text_ar":"اَللّٰهُ اَكْبَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God is great;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, Mgh, Msb;) like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa A^ahowanu Ealayohi","text_ar":"هُوَ اَهْوَنُ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the Kur, xxx. 26,] means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa hay~inN Ealayohi","text_ar":"هُوَ هَيِّنٌ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Az, TA;) but this explanation is of weak authority: (Mgh:) accord. to others, the phrase is elliptical, and means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God is the greatest great"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Az, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God is greater than every"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"other"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"great"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"greater than every"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"other"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"greater than such as that one knows the measure of His majesty:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [or it may be rendered"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God is most great,"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning, greater than any other being:] it is considered as elliptical because it is necessary that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Akbr","text_ar":"اكبر"},{"kind":"text","text":"should have the article"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":", or be followed by a noun in the gen. case [or by the prep."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino","text_ar":"مِنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) In the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aall~`hu A^akobaru kabiyrAF","text_ar":"اَللّٰهُ اَكْبَرُ كَبِيراً"},{"kind":"text","text":", the word"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kbyrA","text_ar":"كبيرا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is put in the accus. case [as a corroborative] in the place of the inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"takobiyrAF","text_ar":"تَكْبِيراً"},{"kind":"text","text":", as though one said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ukab~iru takobiyrFA","text_ar":"اُكَبِّرُ تَكْبِيرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I magnify"},{"kind":"text","text":"Him"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"greatly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"after saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"All~`h Akbr","text_ar":"اللّٰه اكبر"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawomu AlHaj~i AlA^akobari","text_ar":"يَوْمُ الحَجِّ الاَكْبَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The day of the greater pilgrimage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the day of the sacrifice:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the day of 'Arafeh:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and others say otherwise. (TA.) ―         -b4-  In the following words, in a trad. of Mázin,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buEiva nabiY~N mino muDara bidiyni A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"بُعِثَ نَبِىٌّ مِنْ مُضَرَ بِدِينِ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alkubari","text_ar":"الكُبَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", there is an ellipsis, and the meaning is,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bi$aray^iEi diyni A@ll~`hi Alkubari","text_ar":"بِشَرَيِعِ دِينِ ا@للّٰهِ الكُبَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A prophet of Mudar hath been sent with the greatest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"greater,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"great, ordinances of God"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b5-  In a trad. respecting burial,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wayujoEalu A@loA^akobaru mim~aA yaliY A@loqibolapa","text_ar":"وَيُجْعَلُ ا@لْاَكْبَرُ مِمَّا يَلِى ا@لْقِبْلَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And the most excellent shall be placed towards the Kibleh:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, if they be equal [in dignity],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the oldest."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [Agreeably with the former rendering,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akobaru","text_ar":"اَكْبَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur, xxix. 44, is explained as signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Better."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*kr","text_ar":"ذكر"},{"kind":"text","text":".) [And agreeably with the second rendering of the above trad.,] you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA A^akobaru mino zayodK","text_ar":"هٰذَا اَكْبَرُ مِنْ زَيْدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is older than Zeyd."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b6-  In a trad. of Ibn-Ez-Zubeyr, the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daEaA bikuborihi","text_ar":"دَعَا بِكُبْرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He summoned his sheykhs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"elders,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"great men:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kubor","text_ar":"كُبْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"being here [notwithstanding what has been said above,] pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akobaru","text_ar":"اَكْبَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HumorN","text_ar":"حُمْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHomaru","text_ar":"اَحْمَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*ihi AljaAriyapu mino","text_ar":"هٰذِهِ الجَارِيَةُ مِنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuboraY banaAti fulaAnK","text_ar":"كُبْرَى بَنَاتِ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means, ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This girl is of those advanced in age of the daughters of such a one,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino kibaAri banaAtihi","text_ar":"مِنْ كِبَارِ بَنَاتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Ibn-Buzurj.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa A^akobaru qawomihi","text_ar":"هُوَ اَكْبَرُ قَوْمِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kiborapN","text_ar":"كِبْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["Msb","S","K","Mgh","Az","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n36587","headword_ar":"اُكْبُرٌّ","root":"kbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kiborapN","text_ar":"كِبْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}